This tool is used for converting hexadecimal files (either Motorola or 
Intel format) into a binary file. It's a command line tool with basic 
capabilities.

Hex2bin/mot2bin Features

It can handle the extended Intel hex format in segmented and linear address 
modes. Records need not be sorted and there can be gaps between records.  
Holes/unused bytes can be specified as any other value than FF. 
A checksum can be inserted into the binary file.

